15/11/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- In his latest report, the European Parliament's (EP) special rapporteur for Bulgaria, Geoffrey van Orden, recommends that the government take swift and concrete action against organised crime and corruption. The document was submitted Monday (14 November) to the EP's foreign affairs committee, which will assess Bulgaria's preparation for EU membership. 
In a separate report, EP rapporteur for Romania Pierre Moscovici highlighted the fight against corruption, the protection of intellectual property, the strengthening of public administration and environmental protections as the main areas requiring action. (Mediapool, Nine o'clock - 14/11/05)
